info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 20 at 12:59AM PST until January 20 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST TODAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. Locally higher gusts possible on high ridges. * WHERE...Del Norte County and Humboldt County. * WHEN...Until noon PST today. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest gusts expected right along the coast around sunrise..
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
